     1	# Phase 0 Proof Runbook
     2	
     3	## Purpose
     4	
     5	Run and verify a reproducible Phase 0 proof pack that maps every BDD scenario
     6	(`1.1` through `8.1`) to both positive and falsification evidence.
     7	
     8	Canonical BDD source: `docs/rewrite/PHASE0_PROOF_BDD.md`.
     9	
    10	---
    11	
    12	## Prerequisites
    13	
    14	- Repo is checked out at the desired commit.
    15	- Rust toolchain and `cargo-nextest` are installed (same requirements as `just ci`).
    16	- `tanren-cli` and `tanren-mcp` are installed and PATH-callable.
    17	- Python runtime is available through `uv` (for proof helper scripts).
    18	- `jq` is installed and PATH-callable.
    19	
    20	Recommended bootstrap from repo root:
    21	
    22	```bash
    23	uv sync
    24	scripts/runtime/install-runtime.sh
    25	scripts/runtime/verify-installed-runtime.sh
    26	```
    27	
    28	---
    29	
    30	## Hard Cutover Status
    31	
    32	The legacy one-command proof collector (`scripts/proof/phase0/run.sh`) is
    33	retired during Rust testing hard cutover.
    34	
    35	Current behavior-proof commands are:
    36	
    37	```bash
    38	just check-phase0-bdd-smoke
    39	just check-phase0-bdd-wave-a
    40	just check-phase0-mutation-stage
    41	just check-phase0-coverage-stage
    42	just check-phase0-stage-gates
    43	```
    44	
    45	Policy and allowed post-cutover forms:
    46	
    47	- `docs/rewrite/PHASE0_RUST_TEST_CUTOVER_POLICY.md`
    48	
    49	---
    50	
    51	## Verification
    52	
    53	Run explicit verification against an existing pack generated before cutover:
    54	
    55	```bash
    56	scripts/proof/phase0/verify.sh artifacts/phase0-proof/<timestamp>
    57	```
    58	
    59	`verify.sh` fails non-zero when any of these are missing or invalid:
    60	
    61	- `summary.json` / `summary.md`
    62	- `runtime/installed-runtime.json` with `runtime_ok=true`
    63	- positive/falsification `PASS` markers for every scenario `1.1` through `8.1`
    64	- auth/replay supplemental reports
    65	- replay parity + rollback verdicts
    66	- manual walkthrough summary
    67	
    68	---
    69	
    70	## Phase 0 Orchestration Entry Point
    71	
    72	Phase 0 now ships a reusable, non-Python orchestration entrypoint:
    73	
    74	```bash
    75	scripts/orchestration/phase0.sh --spec-id <spec-uuid> --spec-folder <spec-folder>
    76	```
    77	
    78	Behavior contract:
    79	
    80	- Resumes from store truth via `tanren-cli methodology spec status`.
    81	- Autonomous loop runs Phase 0 task/spec gates and agentic phases through
    82	  Codex harness invocation (`codex exec`) only.
    83	- Harness override mode is intentionally disabled in acceptance flow
    84	  (`--harness-cmd` and `TANREN_PHASE0_HARNESS_CMD` are rejected).
    85	- Breaks out only at required human checkpoints:
    86	  - missing spec -> prompt `shape-spec`
    87	  - blocker halt -> prompt `resolve-blockers`
    88	  - walk-ready -> prompt `walk-spec`
    89	- Uses hook commands resolved from `tanren.yml` (task/spec/per-phase hooks)
    90	  and records resolved config in run artifacts under:
    91	  `<spec-folder>/orchestration/phase0/<timestamp>/`.
    92	- Supports output modes via `--output-mode` (or `TANREN_PHASE0_OUTPUT_MODE`):
    93	  - `silent` (default): single-line high-level progress (`task N/M - <verb>`).
    94	  - `quiet`: task definition + deliverable summary + high-level action/result.
    95	  - `verbose`: full command/harness logging.
    96	
    97	Recommended operator flow:
    98	
    99	1. Manually shape the spec (`shape-spec`).
   100	2. Run `scripts/orchestration/phase0.sh ...`.
   101	3. When prompted for walk readiness, manually run `walk-spec`.
   102	
   103	---
   104	
   105	## Staged Gate Scaffolding (Current Non-Blocking Contract)
   106	
   107	While the Rust testing cutover is in progress, staged gate scaffolds are
   108	available in `justfile` and exercised by CI:
   109	
   110	```bash
   111	just check-phase0-scenario-stage
   112	just check-phase0-bdd-smoke
   113	just check-phase0-bdd-wave-a
   114	just check-phase0-mutation-stage
   115	just check-phase0-coverage-stage
   116	just check-phase0-stage-gates
   117	```
   118	
   119	Current behavior:
   120	
   121	- commands are non-blocking scaffolds that emit readiness/status signals,
   122	- `check-phase0-bdd-smoke` executes a cucumber-rs smoke scenario and emits the
   123	  feature tag line as traceability evidence,
   124	- `check-phase0-bdd-wave-a` executes Wave A feature files (`1.1` through `3.2`)
   125	  and emits BEH-tag evidence for each file,
   126	- `check-phase0-mutation-stage` executes a sampled `cargo-mutants` run (when
   127	  installed) and writes machine-readable survivor triage to
   128	  `artifacts/phase0-mutation/staged/latest/triage.json`,
   129	- `check-phase0-coverage-stage` executes staged `cargo llvm-cov` behavior runs
   130	  (when installed) and writes machine-readable behavior-gap classification to
   131	  `artifacts/phase0-coverage/staged/latest/classification.json`,
   132	- they are intended for per-task demonstrability while implementation lands,
   133	- strict blocking enforcement remains a later cutover task.
   134	
   135	---
   136	
   137	## Artifact Layout
   138	
   139	```text
   140	artifacts/phase0-proof/<timestamp>/
   141	  summary.json
   142	  summary.md
   143	  scenarios/
   144	    <scenario-id>/
   145	      positive/
   146	      falsification/
   147	  auth-replay/
   148	    summary.json
   149	  replay-pack/
   150	    source-event-stream.jsonl
   151	    target-task-list.json
   152	    verdicts/
   153	      equivalence.json
   154	      rollback.json
   155	  manual-walkthrough/
   156	    phase-events.jsonl
   157	    summary.json
   158	    steps/
   159	```
   160	
   161	---
   162	
   163	## Reading Results
   164	
   165	1. Open `summary.md` for a human-readable matrix.
   166	2. Open `summary.json` for machine-readable status.
   167	3. For any failing scenario, inspect:
   168	   - `scenarios/<id>/<kind>/command.txt`
   169	   - `scenarios/<id>/<kind>/stdout.log`
   170	   - `scenarios/<id>/<kind>/stderr.log`
   171	
   172	Replay-specific interpretation:
   173	
   174	- `replay-pack/verdicts/equivalence.json`: source vs replayed state parity.
   175	- `replay-pack/verdicts/rollback.json`: invalid replay rejection and no-partial-apply guarantee.
   176	
   177	---
   178	
   179	## Token Troubleshooting
   180	
   181	Token helper:
   182	
   183	```bash
   184	uv run python scripts/proof/phase0/mint_actor_token.py \
   185	  --private-key-pem <path> \
   186	  --issuer tanren-phase0-proof \
   187	  --audience tanren-cli \
   188	  --org-id 00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000000a1 \
   189	  --user-id 00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000000b1 \
   190	  --mode valid \
   191	  --requested-ttl 600 \
   192	  --max-ttl 900 \
   193	  --token-only
   194	```
   195	
   196	The utility always prints computed token math to stderr:
   197	
   198	- `iat`
   199	- `exp`
   200	- `exp_minus_iat`
   201	- configured `max_ttl`
   202	
   203	Invariant enforced:
   204	
   205	- non-`ttl_over_max` modes fail when `exp_minus_iat > actor_token_max_ttl_secs`
   206	
   207	Operational rule:
   208	
   209	- derive `exp` from `iat` (`exp = iat + requested_ttl`), not from independent wall-clock math.
   210	
   211	---
   212	
   213	## CI + Ship Gate
   214	
   215	After proof pack generation and verification:
   216	
   217	```bash
   218	just ci
   219	lefthook run pre-commit
   220	```
   221	
   222	Then stage/commit/push with a clean `git status`.

